commit.message: libbladeRF: fix up sync TX initialization bug

libbladeRF: added cmake find_package() support

Fixes #418

Addresses #947

cmake: defines for MSVC

doc: bladeRF-cli: clarify K/M/G as powers of 1024

Fixes #840
windows: add a few missing depencies
libbladeRF_test: bump dependency

test: txrx_hwloop: fix getopt_long warning by changing 'c' to int

Resolved the compiler warning caused by comparing
getopt_long's return value with a char. Changed 'c'
from char to int to correctly handle -1 return values.

Fixes #952

test: device test label turned into libbladeRF label

Not really a need to separate tests as libbladeRF is intended to
interface with the device.

test: python virtual environment setup added to build output

The setup_env.sh and requirements.txt files are copied to build/output.

Ex:
$ ./output/setup_env.sh
$ source nuand/bin/activate
$ python ./output/libbladeRF_test_txrx_hwloop.py

libbladeRF: fix assignment between very fast and very slow sample rates

Failure info:
Failed going from 48,601,811 -> 1,228,911 MSPS.
Worked when first sample rate is < 40,000,001 MSPS.
Worked when the subsequent sample rate is > 2,083,334 MSPS.

test: rx_timestamp_tb: continuous run support

test: rx_timestamp_tb: MIMO support

Divides the expected meta value data by 2 when MIMO enabled.

test: rx_timestamp_tb: meta_verify process iteration limit added

This circumvents the rst asserted in the tb.

host: CMake minimum version bump to 3.5

Accommodates the following warning issued by CMake v3.27.1.

CMake Deprecation Warning:
  Compatibility with CMake < 3.5 will be removed from a 
  future version of CMake.

test: fx3_gpif_meta_8bit_tb: corrected adc_streams().data_v behavior

adc_streams(0 and 1).data_v engages regardless of which module is
enabled in libbladeRF.
test: rx_timestamp_tb: removed redudent FIFO tests in other test benches

test: fx3_gpif_meta_8bit_tb: last_ts re-initializes after reset asserted

Iterator added to meta spacing check. This allows for last_ts to
re-initialize after the reset to fifo_writer is asserted.
hdl: FPGA patch update v0.15.3

hdl: fifo_writer: proper META state transition for exclusive ch1 usage

Addresses an issue where the META state was not transitioning correctly
when only channel 1 (ch1) was enabled. The fix ensures that the META
state now correctly exits the META_WRITE state and enters the
META_DOWNCOUNT state when ch1 is exclusively enabled.

test: fx3_gpif_iq_8bit_tb: adc_stream values checked directly for 16b

The 8b samples leave off the last 3 samples of the ADC.
Fixes 16b mode tests.
